title: NoCameraSound
description: Need to take a screenshot or record a video without all the noise? NoCameraSound IPA has got you covered! This powerful app allows you to easily mute the shutter sound or video recording sound on your device, making it perfect for situations where you need to be discreet. And the best part? NoCameraSound is compatible with iOS versions 15-15.7.1 and 16.0-16.1.2, and can be used on a non-jailbroken device. It’s especially useful for Japanese users, who are not able to turn off the camera sound by default. Give NoCameraSound a try and enjoy a quiet, hassle-free photography experience.

title: Blacklist
description: Remove the blacklist from your device, allows you to use apps freely! Compatible with 14.0 - 15.7.1 & 16.0 - 16.1.2 (iOS 14 requires Troll Store).

title: Gameplay Color
description: Gameplay Color, developed by Jason Morley, is a JavaScript Game Boy Color emulator for iOS, based on the GameBoy-Online emulator core that installs as a web clip and allows you to play ROM games through your browser just as any other emulator app.

title: RecordScreen
description: RecordScreen is a universal iPhone and iPad application that allows you to record your screen, even on non-jailbroken devices. It was created by a young developer named Nicolas Gomollon. This application was made from RecordMyScreen’s open source and does the same things that RecordMyScreen does, that is, record your screen. The difference in the two is that the design and interface of the application was made from scratch by Nicolas. Choosing between this application and RecordMyScreen is purely based on personal preference.

title: RecordMyScreen
description: RecordMyScreen is an iOS screen recorder created by a talented developer that goes by the name of CoolStar, one of the first people to bring screen recording to any non-jailbroken device. RecordMyScreen was the first free, open source screen recorder for iOS. It was developed capable of running on both jailbroken and non-jailbroken devices. Although CoolStar created the initial code, many people have joined in and helped create the RecordMyScreen we see today. Some of these talented people are Protosphere (@protosphere_), John Coates (@punksomething), Brandon Etheredge (@brandonEtheredg), Nicolas Gomollon (@gomollon), and Aditya KD (@caughtinflux).

title: Xina
description: Supports iOS 15.0 - 15.1.1 and A12+ devices

title: 2600emu
description: Advanced open-source Atari 2600 VCS emulator based on Stella with a minimalist UI and a focus on low audio/video latency, supporting a wide variety of devices from the original Xperia Play to modern devices like the Nvidia Shield and Pixel phones.

title: RetroArch
description: RetroArch is an open source, frontend for emulators. Thanks to a group of talented developers, the emulator has been ported to mobile that works as a hub of unified, emulated platforms that allow you to play a ton of games ranging from things such as GBA, NES, SNES, N64, Genesis, PS1, and so much more.

title: gpSPhone
description: gpSPhone is one of the best GBA emualtors for legacy iOS. It was created by ZodTTD for jailbroken devices since the iOS5+ era but it is now possible to install using enterprise.
